      <td>[[Body movement supports spatial reasoning</td>
      <td>Spatial reasoning]] forces the individual to abstract away from features perceived through individual modalities, such as brightness and loudness, and derive an [[Physical and conceptual spaces are coded in the same region</td>
      <td>independent spatial representation]]. Due to this, spatial reasoning is conceptually located at the confluence of all the bodily senses.</td>
